body_html:
Could you try the nightly build and also other older versions and see if we can narrow it down to just that build?

It looks like your version of Python does not have UCS4 unicode checked in, see e.g.
https://groups.google.com/forum/#!topic/comp.lang.python/9dThp1h3TMM

Can you do?

>>> import sys
>>> print sys.maxunicode

and see what it returns (see e.g. http://stackoverflow.com/questions/1446347/how-to-find-out-if-python-is-compiled-with-ucs-2-or-ucs-4)

body:
Could you try the nightly build and also other older versions and see if we can narrow it down to just that build?

It looks like your version of Python does not have UCS4 unicode checked in, see e.g.
https://groups.google.com/forum/#!topic/comp.lang.python/9dThp1h3TMM

Can you do?

```
>>> import sys
>>> print sys.maxunicode
```

and see what it returns (see e.g. http://stackoverflow.com/questions/1446347/how-to-find-out-if-python-is-compiled-with-ucs-2-or-ucs-4)
